<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,258,715]" box="[151,1319,258,283]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Black. Labium and apical area of forewing light brown. Hind legs with dark brown to black macrosetae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,258,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[199,373,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with caudal angle almost truncate, ventral margin straight with long stout setae on caudal 0.33. Subgenital plate with long hair-like setae. Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme, shaft of uniform width in basal 0.75 length, then narrowed, apex hooked, with lateral feebly serrated flanges, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,258,715]" box="[199,441,438,463]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[199,284,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Length.</emphasis>
