<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,258,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[324,518,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalayensis">
<emphasis box="[324,518,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to several species, all predominantly black with the apical area of the forewing paler and with a relatively slender body (see under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[866,983,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvata">
<emphasis box="[866,880,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[898,983,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">curvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[1211,1407,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalayensis">
<emphasis box="[1211,1407,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[263,366,655,678]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noctua">
<emphasis box="[263,277,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[290,366,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">noctua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has more prominent lateral flanges and the apical hook of the aedeagal shaft is more slender in 
<taxonomicName box="[180,283,692,715]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noctua">
<emphasis box="[180,283,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. noctua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to that in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[514,707,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghalayensis">
<emphasis box="[514,707,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. meghalayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
